verses.roman:
kulīna-grāmī rāmānanda, satyarāja khāṅna
tāṅre ājñā dila prabhu kariyā sammāna

synonyms: kulīna-grāmī—the inhabitants of the village known as Kulīna-grāma; rāmānanda—Rāmānanda; satyarāja khāṅna—Satyarāja Khān; tāṅre—to them; ājñā dila—gave an order; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; kariyā sammāna—showing great respect.
translation: Rāmānanda and Satyarāja Khān were present from Kulīna-grāma, and Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, with great respect, gave them the following orders.
